commit.message:
CI: remove rack monkey patches

Very old, serves no purpose anymore.

CI: `rdiscount` 2.2.7.3 resolved the TruffleRuby issue

See https://github.com/davidfstr/rdiscount/issues/159
CI: use the released version of `childprocess`

CI: no need to set `RUBY_ENGINE`

It should be defined on every Ruby we use, if it isn't, setting it to
"ruby" would probably not be correct.

CI: no need to set `Encoding.default_external`

According to documentation you should not set it:
https://ruby-doc.org/core-2.6/Encoding.html#method-c-default_external-3D

Remove `Rack::Protection::EncryptedCookie` (#1989)

The rack-session gem has equivalent functionality.

Close https://github.com/sinatra/sinatra/issues/1945

commit.message:
Remove the `IndifferentHash` initializer (#1982)

See these links for background:
- https://github.com/sinatra/sinatra/pull/1951
- https://github.com/sinatra/sinatra/issues/1948

Before

    > Sinatra::IndifferentHash.new(a: 1)[:b]
    => {"a"=>1}

After

    > Sinatra::IndifferentHash.new(a: 1)[:b]
    => {:a=>1}

Close #1953

commit.message:
CI: use improved version of `childprocess` gem (#1980)

Use the awesome pull request by eregon: https://github.com/enkessler/childprocess/pull/175
that uses native Process.spawn on all platforms

JVM rubies can't use the default fork+exec approach in childprocess, so
we fall back to CHILDPROCESS_POSIX_SPAWN, but that is not available on
aarch64 (me using Docker on Apple silicon). Annoying when debugging
tests.

(This should still work even after the PR is merged and the branch
removed)

commit.message:
Ruby 3.3 + Bundler 2.5 compatibility

Sinatra needs to account for the bundled gems warning system. Probably
since https://github.com/ruby/ruby/pull/9148.

Add test for classic app using Zeitwerk, as it was so similar and none
was added in https://github.com/sinatra/sinatra/pull/1831.
Helpful message when `Sinatra::Runner` times out

Shorter `Sinatra::Runner` timeout

It should never take near 30 seconds for a server to be alive.
